(116, 'NEWS @ 10 SEPT 18TH', '<p><strong><u>NEWS AT 10 AM </u></strong><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>SEPT. 18TH, 2017</u></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><u>HEADLINES AT 10 AM</u></strong></p>\r\n<p># PRESIDENT BUHARI IN NEW YORK, FOR THE 72ND SESSION OF UNITED NATIONS GENERAL ASSEMBLY.</p>\r\n<p># NIGERIAN AIRFORCE REITERATES DETERMINATION TO DISCHARGE ITS CONSTITUTIONAL RESPONSIBILITY EFFECTIVELY.</p>\r\n<p># NIGERIANS CONTINUE TO REACT TO PROSCRIPTION OF IPOB ACTIVITIES BY SOUTH EAST GOVERNORS.</p>\r\n<p>THANKS FOR JOINING US ON THE NEWS AT TEN ON NTA NEWS 24. I AM ADEYEMI OMOJOLA FATOBA.</p>\r\n<p><strong><u>BUHARI ARRIVES NEW YORK</u></strong></p>\r\n<p>PRESIDENT MUHAMMADU BUHARI IS IN NEW YORK AHEAD OF THE OPENING OF 72ND SESSION OF THE UNITED NATIONS GENERAL ASSEMBLY.</p>\r\n<p>STATE HOUSE CORRESPONDENT ADAMU SAMBO REPORTS ON THE 3RD OUTING OF THE NIGERIAN LEADER AT THE GLOBAL&nbsp;&nbsp;ANNUAL EVENT SINCE COMING TO POWER.</p>\r\n<p><strong><u>&nbsp;</u></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><u>OUTCOME OF SOUTH EAST GOVERNORS MEETING</u></strong></p>\r\n<p>THE SOUTH-EAST GOVERNOR&rsquo;S FORUM HAS REINFORCED THEIR DESIRES IN THE RESTRUCTURING OF NIGERIA WHERE ALL THE NATIONAL ISSUES WILL BE DISCUSSED AND SETTLED AMICABLY.</p>\r\n<p>CHAIRMAN OF THE FORUM AND EBONYI STATE GOVERNOR, DAVID UMAHI IN A MEDIA BRIEFING ANNOUNCED THE PROSCRIPTION OF THE INDIGENOUS PEOPLE OF BIAFRA IPOB.</p>\r\n<p>KINGSLEY OKORO REPORTS.</p>\r\n<p><strong><u>LAI MOHAMMED ON IPOB</u></strong></p>\r\n<p>INFORMATION AND CULTURE MINISTER LAI MOHAMMED SAYS THE ACTIVITIES OF IPOB IS A SPONSORED PLOT TO DISCREDIT PRESIDENT MUHAMMADU BUHARI''S ADMINISTRATION AND DIVERT THE PEOPLE&rsquo;S ATTENTION FROM THE ACHIEVEMENTS OF GOVERNMENT.</p>\r\n<p>THE MINISTER STATED THIS AT A MEDIA BRIEFING IN LAGOS.</p>\r\n<p>ANTHONY FORSON REPORTS.</p>\r\n<p><strong><u>VOX POP ON IPOB PROSCRIBTION</u></strong></p>\r\n<p>FOLLOWING THE PROSCRIPTION OF THE ACTIVITIES OF</p>\r\n<p>INDIGENOUS PEOPLE OF BIAFRA BY THE SOUTH EAST</p>\r\n<p>GOVERNORS, NIGERIANS HAVE BEEN REACTING TO THE</p>\r\n<p>DEVELOPMENT.</p>\r\n<p><strong>TRACK UP</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><u>POP AT NDA</u></strong></p>\r\n<p>THE PRESIDENCY HAS TASKED THE NIGERIAN ARMED FORCES TO COLLABORATE WITH THE PRIVATE SECTOR FOR CREATIVITY AND INNOVATION IN SCIENCE AND TECHNOLOGY TO EFFECTIVELY DEAL WITH SECURITY THREATS EMANATING FROM GROWING SOPHISTICATION OF MISCREANTS IN THE USE OF INTERNET AND OTHER DEVICES.</p>\r\n<p>THE PRESIDENT STATED THIS IN A MESSAGE DELIVERED BY VICE PRESIDENT YEMI OSINBAJO AT THE COMBINED GRADUATION OF CADETS 64<sup>TH</sup> AND 65<sup>TH</sup> OF THE NIGERIAN DEFENCE ACADEMY KADUNA.</p>\r\n<p>SULEIMAN ABDULLAHI RIGACHIKUN REPORTS.</p>\r\n<p><strong><u>CAS ON OPERATION RUWAN WUTA</u></strong></p>\r\n<p>THE NIGERIAN AIRFORCE SAYS IT WILL NOT ALLOW ANY INDIVIDUAL OR GROUP OF PERSONS TO INTERFERE WITH ITS CONSTITUTIONAL RESPONSIBILITY OF UPHOLDING THE NATION&rsquo;S SOVEREIGNTY.</p>\r\n<p>CHIEF OF AIR STAFF AIR MARSHAL SADIQUE ABUBAKAR REITERATED THIS WHILE REVIEWING ON-GOING OPERATIONS OF THE AIRFORCE IN THE NORTH EAST.</p>\r\n<p>DEFENCE CORRESPONDENT ISAAC NKUMA REPORTS.</p>\r\n<p><strong><u>&nbsp;</u></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><u>NIS/PARTNER NETHERLAND ON BORDERS</u></strong></p>\r\n<p>A DELEGATION FROM NETHERLANDS IS IN NIGERIA TO OFFER TRAINING TO IMMIGRATION OFFICERS ON INTERNATIONAL BEST PRACTICES FOR ENTRY AND EXIT POINTS AT NATIONAL BORDERS.</p>\r\n<p>THE ONE DAY TRAIN- THE -TRAINER WORKSHOP NAMED &ldquo;HORSEMANSHIP&rdquo; IS FOR SUPERINTENDENTS AND ASSISTANT CONTROLLERS GENERAL OF IMMIGRATION.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;MURJANATU ADAM SA&rsquo;EED REPORTS</p>\r\n<p><strong><u>&nbsp;</u></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><u>PROMO 1 @ 10 AM</u></strong></p>\r\n<p>YOU ARE WATCHING THE NEWS AT TEN ON NTA NEWS 24. TIME FOR A SHORT BREAK</p>\r\n<p><strong>MORE NEWS WHEN WE RETURN, </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><u>CHIBOK GIRLS SEND FORTH</u></strong></p>\r\n<p>THE TRAUMA AND PSYCOLOGICAL TORTURE ENDURED BY THE ABDUCTED CHIBOK GIRLS IS GRADAULLY BECOMING A THING OF THE PAST AS SOME OF THE RELEASED GIRLS TAKE THE NEXT STEP IN THEIR LIVES, AFTER UNDERGOING EIGTH MONTHS REHABILITATION PROGRAM.</p>\r\n<p>MOMSO DAMIAN DATTI WAS AT THE SEND FORTH CEREMONY ORGANISED TO URSHER THEM INTO NORMAL LIFE.</p>\r\n<p><strong><u>SPECIAL ON SECURITY IMPLICATION OF&nbsp; CATTLE RUSTLING </u></strong></p>\r\n<p>CATTLE RUSTTLING, FARMERS AND HERDERS CONFLICT HAVE&nbsp; OVER TIME BECOME A RECURRING SECURITY CHALLENGE IN NIGERIA.</p>\r\n<p>SEVERAL EFFORTS AT FACILITATING DIALOGUE THROUGH THE SEARCH FOR COMMON GROUND AND PEACE BUILDING HAVE YIELDED LITTLE RESULTS.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>EXPERTS&nbsp; ARE HOWEVER OF THE VIEW THAT THERE IS A DISCONNECT BETWEEN FARMERS,HERDERS,RESEARCHERS AND POLICY MAKERS WHICH MUST BE BRIDGED FOR BETTER UNDERSTANDING OF DIFFERENCES&nbsp; BY CONFLICTING PARTIES</p>\r\n<p>LYDIA SAMSON HAS THE REPORT</p>\r\n<p><strong><u>FCT EMERGENCY SECURITY MEETING</u></strong></p>\r\n<p>IN THE WAKE OF THE SECURITY SITUATION IN THE SOUTH EAST OF THE COUNTRY, FCT MINISTER MUHAMMADU MUSA BELLO HAS CONVENED AN EMERGENCY FCT SECURITY COMMITTEE MEETING.</p>\r\n<p>MITAIRE IKPEN REPORTS THAT THE MINISTER SAYS MACHINERIES ARE IN PLACE TO ENSURE SECURITY OF LIVES AND PROPERTY IN THE TERRITORY.</p>\r\n<p><strong><u>NASARAWA GOVT SETS UP SECURITY COMMAND CENTRE</u></strong></p>\r\n<p>IN AN EFFORT TO TAKE PRECAUTIONARY MEASURES AGAINST BREAK DOWN OF LAW AND ORDER FOLLOWING SECURITY BREACHES IN SOME PARTS OF THE COUNTRY, GOVERNOR UMARU TANKO AL MAKURA HAS SET UP A SECURITY COMMAND CENTRE IN LAFIA.</p>\r\n<p>THIS IS AFTER AN EMERGENCY MEETING BETWEEN THE GOVERNOR AND ALL HEADS OF SECURITY AGENCIES AS WELL AS LEADERS OF IGBO COMMUNITY IN THE STATE.</p>\r\n<p>JOSHUA OJITO REPORTS</p>\r\n<p><strong><u>PDP SHERIFF FACTION DEFECT TO APC</u></strong></p>\r\n<p>ONE OF THE CHIEFTAINS IN THE ALI MODU SHERIFF LED PDP FACTION THAT WAS SACKED BY THE SUPREME COURT, DR. CAIRO OJUOGBO HAS DECAMPED TO APC, WITH A MAMMOTH CROWD OF SUPPORTERS.</p>\r\n<p>THELMA ELIOGU REPORTS THAT THE EVENT WHICH TOOK PLACE IN AGBOR WITNESSED THE TURNOUT OF NOTABLE PROGRESSIVES, AMONG THEM, THE MINISTER OF STATE FOR PETROLEUM, IBE KACHIKWU AND OLOROGUN OTEGA EMEROH.</p>\r\n<p><strong><u>&nbsp;</u></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><u>&nbsp;</u></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><u>CONSERVING BIOSPHERE RESERVES</u></strong></p>\r\n<p>THE FEDERAL GOVERNMENT HAS PROPOSED TWO NATIONAL SITES AND TWO TRANS-BOUNDARY AREAS BETWEEN NIGERIA AND CAMEROUN TO BECOME BIOSPHERE RESERVES.</p>\r\n<p>MINISTER OF ENVIRONMENT IBRAHIM USMAN JIBRIL SAID THIS AT THE 5<sup>TH</sup> SESSION OF THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF AFRICAN NETWORK OF MAN AND BIOSPHERE RESERVES IN IBADAN.</p>\r\n<p>AISHA BELLO REPORTS.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><u>CJN SWEARS IN ACTING CJ FOR FEDREAL HIGH COURT</u></strong></p>\r\n<p>CHIEF JUSTICE OF NIGERIA <strong>JUSTICE WALTER ONNOGHEN</strong> HAS TOLD THE NATION''S JUDICIARY NOT TO ALLOW ITSELF TO BE BLACKMAILED OR INTIMIDATED BY THE ANTICS AND COMMENTS OF DESPERATE LITIGANTS.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;HE SAID THIS WHILE SWEARING IN THE ACTING CHIEF JUDGE OF THE FEDERAL HIGH COURT, <strong>JUSTICE ABDUL KAFARATI.</strong></p>\r\n<p>JUDICIARY CORRESPONDENT FEMI OKEOWO REPORTS</p>\r\n<p><strong><u>VP AT BOOK LAUNCH</u></strong></p>\r\n<p>VICE PRESIDENT YEMI OSINBAJO SAYS NIGERIAN YOUTHS REMAIN THE GREATEST ASSEST WHICH GIVES THE RAY OF HOPE.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;THE VICE PRESIDENT WAS SPEAKING AT THE UNVEILING OF A MOTIVATIONAL BOOK IN ABUJA TITLED &ldquo;ACTIVATING SUCCESS&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>STATE HOUSE CORRESPONDENT JIDE ONIFADE REPORTS.</p>\r\n<p><strong><u>FREE EYE SURGERY</u></strong></p>\r\n<p>OVER ONE THOUSAND PEOPLE WITH DIFFERENT EYE AILMENTS ESPECIALLY CATARACT HAVE BENEFITTED IN KANO FROM THE SERVICES OFFERED BY THE WIFE OF THE FORMER VICE PRESIDENT AMINA NAMADI SAMBO AS PART OF ACTIVITIES MARKING TEN YEAR&rsquo;S OF &ldquo;I- CARE WOMEN AND YOUTH INITIATIVE&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>ALI ADAMU REPORTS THAT THE EYE SURGERY EXERCISE WILL LAST ONE WEEK.</p>\r\n<p><strong><u>MWAN COMMUNITY OUTREACH</u></strong></p>\r\n<p>MORE THAN 200 WOMEN AND CHILDREN OF PIWOYI COMMUNITY, A SUBURB OF ABUJA HAVE RECEIVED FREE MEDICAL ATTENTION FROM THE MEDICAL WOMEN ASSOCIATION OF NIGERIA (MWAN).</p>\r\n<p>VICTOR AZU REPORTS THAT THE GESTURE IS PART OF EVENTS COMMEMORATING THE ASSOCIATION&rsquo;S 40<sup>TH</sup> ANNIVERSARY AND 20<sup>TH</sup> BIENNIAL CONFERENCE.</p>\r\n<p><strong><u>PROMO 2 @ 10AM</u></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;YOU ARE STILL WATCHING THE NEWS AT TEN ON NTA NEWS 24, IT IS TIME FOR ANOTHER BREAK , AND WHEN WE RETURN,</p>\r\n<p># COCOA PRODUCTION EXPECTED TO REBOUND IN THE NEXT PLANTING SEASON, THAT WILL BE IN BUSINESS NEWS</p>\r\n<p>STAY WITH US.</p>\r\n<p><strong><u>BUSINESS NEWS @ 10AM</u></strong></p>\r\n<p>COCOA PRODUCTION&nbsp; IN NIGERIA IS EXPECTED TO SEE REBOUNDING IN 2017/2018 PLANTING SEASON.</p>\r\n<p>LET US JOIN AMINA NOUJAIM ON BUSINESS NEWS FOR DETAILS AND MORE BUSINESS NEWS STORIES.</p>\r\n<p><strong><u>WATER MINISTER COMMISSIONS NAWIS CENTRE</u></strong></p>\r\n<p>THE MINISTRY OF WATER RESOURCES WILL ALWAYS EMBRACE INITIATIVES THAT WILL AID THE DEVELOPMENT OF THE WATER SECTOR.</p>\r\n<p>THE MINISTER OF WATER RESOURCES, SULEIMAN ADAMU GAVE THE ASSURANCE AT THE OPENING OF THE NATIONAL WATER RESOURCES INFORMATION SYSTEM (NAWIS) CENTRE IN ABUJA.</p>\r\n<p>MUHAMMED GARBA NATA''ALA THE REPORT.</p>\r\n<p><strong><u>&nbsp;</u></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><u>&nbsp;</u></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><u>SENATE COMMITTEE ON WORKS VISITS NIGER STATE</u></strong></p>\r\n<p>THE SENATE COMMITTEE ON WORKS HAS CHARGED CONTRACTORS HANDLING FEDERAL GOVERNMENT PROJECTS IN NIGER STATE TO EXECUTE THE PROJECTS ACCORDING TO SPECIFICATIONS AND MEET UP WITH THE COMPLETION PERIOD.</p>\r\n<p>CHAIRMAN OF THE COMMITTEE, SENATOR KABIRU IBRAHIM GAYA GAVE THE DIRECTIVE WHILE ON AN OVERSIGHT TOUR OF ONGOING FEDERAL GOVERNMENT PROJECTS IN THE STATE.</p>\r\n<p>MUKTAR ABUBAKAR WOWO REPORTS.</p>\r\n<p><strong><u>TATA BRIDGE RECONSTRUCTION</u></strong></p>\r\n<p>CONTRACTORS HANDLING THE TWO BILLION NAIRA RECONSTRUCTION WORK ON THE COLLAPSED TATABU BRIDGE AND THE EIGHT HUNDRED MILLION NAIRA BOKANI BRIDGE IN MOKWA LOCAL GOVERNMENT AREA OF NIGER STATE HAVE ASSURED OF SPEEDY COMPLETION OF THE PROJECTS EXPECTED TO BE CONCLUDED BY DECEMBER THIS YEAR.</p>\r\n<p>DAUDA MOHAMMED HAS AN UPDATE ON THE SITUATION</p>\r\n<p>AT THE TWO SITES.</p>\r\n<p><strong><u>&nbsp;</u></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><u>&nbsp;</u></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><u>&nbsp;</u></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><u>NAHCON COMMENDS NTA</u></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>THE NIGERIAN TELEVISION AUTHORITY HAS RECEIVED A PAT ON THE BACK FOR THE PROFESSIONAL AND PATRIOTIC MANNER IN WHICH IT COVERED THE 2017 HAJJ PILGRIMAGE IN SAUDI ARABIA.</p>\r\n<p>CHAIRMAN OF THE NATIONAL HAJJ COMMISSION OF NIGERIA ABDULLAHI MUKHTAR AT A PARLEY WITH MEDIA PRACTITIONERS IN MAKKAH SAUDI ARABIA SAYS THE NTA HAS ONCE AGAIN DEMONSTRATED HER CAPABILTY IN TELEVISION BROADCASTING.</p>\r\n<p>ABDULLAHI MUSTAPHA REPORTS</p>\r\n<p><strong><u>&nbsp;</u></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><u>BUHARI FRIENDS HOLDS SOUTH-SOUTH JOINT PRAYERS</u></strong></p>\r\n<p>NIGERIANS HAVE BEEN CHARGED TO LIVE IN PEACE AND UNITY WHILE SUPPORTING THE GOVERNMENT TO FIGHT CORRUPTION AND TERRORISM TO ENHANCE A STRONGER ECONOMIC &nbsp;STRUCTURE OF THE NATION.</p>\r\n<p>THESE WERE THE SUBMISSIONS OF KEY PLAYERS IN CALABAR AT THE SOUTH-SOUTH JOINT PRAYER SUMMIT ORGANIZED BY BUHARI FRIENDS ORGANIZATION NETWORK IN NIGERIA AND DIASPORA FOR PRESIDENT MUHAMMADUBUHARI AND THE NATION.</p>\r\n<p>MAUREEN LEO AJOM HAS DETAILS.</p>\r\n<p><strong><u>NIGERIAN REBIRTH PROJECT VISIT NTA</u></strong></p>\r\n<p>THEIR COLLECTIVE PASSION TO TURN AROUND THE</p>\r\n<p>NATION&rsquo;S FORTUNES LED THEM TO THE NIGERIA</p>\r\n<p>TELEVISION AUTHORITY TO LET THE WORLD KNOW THAT</p>\r\n<p>ACHIEVEMENT OF A CREATIVE MIND HAS NO LIMIT.</p>\r\n<p>ABDULLAHI SULAYMAN IYAJI REPORTS ON THE VISIT OF</p>\r\n<p>TWO GROUPS TO THE NTA.</p>\r\n<p><strong><u>&nbsp;</u></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><u>RECAP @ 10 aM</u></strong></p>\r\n<p>NEWS AT 10 IS BROADCAST LIVE ON NTA NEWS 24. ANOTHER LOOK AT THE TOP STORIES.</p>\r\n<p># PRESIDENT BUHARI IN NEW YORK, FOR THE 72ND SESSION OF UNITED NATIONS GENERAL ASSEMBLY.</p>\r\n<p># NIGERIAN AIRFORCE REITERATES DETERMINATION TO DISCHARGE ITS CONSTITUTIONAL RESPONSIBILITY EFFECTIVELY.</p>\r\n<p># NIGERIANS CONTINUE TO REACT TO PROSCRIPTION OF IPOB ACTIVITIES BY SOUTH EAST GOVERNORS.</p>\r\n<p><strong>STAY WITH US</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><u>SPORTS AT TEN</u></strong></p>\r\n<p>NOW TO SPORTS, HOME BASED EAGLES CLASH WITH BLACK STARS OF GHANA IN THE WAFU CUP OF NATIONS JUST AS THE MANCHESTER CLUBS REACH IDENTICAL RECORD AT THE TOP OF THE ENGLISH PREMIER LEAGUE.</p>\r\n<p>LET&rsquo;S JOIN SPORTS DESK FOR DETAILS.</p>\r\n<p><strong><u>FOREIGN AT 10AM</u></strong></p>\r\n<p>U.N SECRETARY SAYS PRESSURE NEEDED TO STOP MYANMAR CARNAGE.</p>\r\n<h1>ALSO, HAMAS SAYS IT IS READY TO HOLD FIRST ELECTIONS SINCE 2006.</h1>\r\n<h1>FROM THE FOREIGN DESK, GARBA MUHAMMAD NATA&rsquo;ALA HAS MORE DETAILS.</h1>\r\n<p><strong><u>E ! ON CHIGUL</u></strong></p>\r\n<p>IN THE RAVE OF THE BIG SUCCESS OF THE HILARIOUS MOVIE, BANANA ISLAND GHOST, CHIGUL DROPS THE VISUALS FOR HER TRACK TITLED "BLESSING".</p>\r\n<p>ABDULMALIK ADIO TELLS US MORE ON ARTS AND ENTERTAINMENT</p>\r\n<p><strong><u>CLOSING </u></strong></p>\r\n<p>THAT CONCLUDES THE NEWS AT 10 ON NTA NEWS 24, JOIN ME AT THE TOP OF THE HOUR FOR AN UPDATE OF THE NEWS, I AM ADEYEMI OMOJOLA FATOBA, THANKS FOR YOUR TIME.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 2, '2017-09-20 05:53:13'),
(117, 'NNPC ASSURES NIGERIANS OF ADEQUATE PRODUCTS.', '<p><strong><u>NNPC ASSURES NIGERIANS OF ADEQUATE PRODUCTS. COPY </u></strong></p>\r\n<p>THE NIGERIAN NATIONAL PETROLEUM CORPORATION, NNPC, HAS ASSURED THE PUBLIC NOT TO ENGAGE IN</p>\r\n<p>GRAPHICS&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>PANIC BUYING OF PETROLEUM PRODUCTS THAT THEY HAVE ENOUGH TO SERVE THE NATION FOR 48 DAYS.</p>\r\n<p>THIS IS CONTAINED IN A STATEMENT BY THE</p>\r\n<p>CORPORATIONS, GROUP GENERAL MANAGER PUBLIC</p>\r\n<p>AFFAIRS NDU UGHAMADU.</p>\r\n<p>NNPC THEREFORE ADVISED MOTORISTS TO REPORT ANY</p>\r\n<p>CHALLENGE IN THE COURSE OF PURCHASING TO THE</p>\r\n<p>DEPARTMENT OF PETROLEUM RESOURCES, DPR.</p>\r\n<p>IN A SIMILAR PRESS RELEASE NDU UGHAMADU SAID THE</p>\r\n<p>FIRE AT THE APAPA LOADING JETTY, LAGOS WOULD NOT</p>\r\n<p>AFFECT THE SUPPLY OF THE PRODUCTS.</p>\r\n<p>IN EXPLAINED THAT THE FIRE SPARKED OFF FROM THE</p>\r\n<p>ACTIVITIES OF HOODLUMS WHO WERE SCOOPING FUELS</p>\r\n<p>SPILLED FROM A SHIP DISCHARGING FUEL AT THE JETTY.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 20, '2017-09-20 06:05:52'),
(118, 'NEWS LOG FOR GOOD MORNING NIGERIA', '<p><strong><u>GOOD MORNING NIGERIA</u></strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong><u>SEPT 18TH, 2017</u></strong></p>\r\n<p>HEADLINES ON GMN</p>\r\n<p>PRESENTERS ON CAM</p>\r\n<p>MAIN NEWS FOR GMN, MON 18<sup>TH</sup> SEPT. 2017</p>\r\n<p>BUHARI ARRIVES NEW YORK</p>\r\n<p>CONSERVING BIOSPHERE RESERVES</p>\r\n<p>SENATE COMMITTEE ON WORKS VISITS NIGER STATE</p>\r\n<p>NAHCON COMMENDS NTA</p>\r\n<p>OUTCOME OF SOUTH EAST GOVERNORS MEETING</p>\r\n<p>LAI MOHAMMED ON IPOB</p>\r\n<p>FREE EYE SURGERY</p>\r\n<p>NIGERIAN REBIRTH PROJECT VISIT NTA</p>\r\n<p>CLOSING</p>\r\n<p>1<sup>ST </sup>BREAK---5.00MINS</p>\r\n<p>BUSINESS INTRO</p>\r\n<p>NEWSPAPER STING</p>\r\n<p>NEWSPAPER REVIEW</p>\r\n<p>TAKE STING FOR &lsquo;FROM THE PAPERS&rsquo;</p>\r\n<p>INTRODUCE BAYO ATOYEBI..NEWSPAPER REVIEWER</p>\r\n<p>2<sup>ND</sup> BREAK---4.26MINS</p>\r\n<p>1<sup>ST</sup>&nbsp; TOPIC</p>\r\n<p>BACKGROUND REPORT ON MILITARY IN SOUTH EAST</p>\r\n<p>INTRODUCTION OF GUESTS</p>\r\n<p>QUESTIONS FOR MILITARY IN SOUTH EAST</p>\r\n<p>SIGN OFF GUEST AND TAKE A BREAK.</p>\r\n<p>2<sup>ND</sup> TOPIC</p>\r\n<p>3<sup>RD</sup> BREAK----2.30MINS</p>\r\n<p>GMN BACK GROUNDER ON INDUSTRIAL RELATIONS</p>\r\n<p>GUESTS FOR MANAGING INDUSTRIAL RELATIONS</p>\r\n<p>QUESTIONS FOR GUESTS</p>\r\n<p>SPORTS FOR GMN</p>\r\n<p>FOREIGN FOR GMN</p>\r\n<p>GMN E ! ON CHIGUL</p>\r\n<p>WEATHER FOR MONDAY</p>\r\n<p>CLOSING</p>', 20, '2017-09-20 06:08:56'),
(119, 'BASKET BALL CORRECT', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>NIGERIA SENIOR MEN&rsquo;S BASKETBALL TEAM, D&rsquo;TIGERS, HAVE BEEN DETHRONED AS CHAMPIONS OF AFRICA AFTER BEING BEATEN 77-65 BY TUNISIA IN THE FINAL OF THE 2017 AFROBASKET TOURNAMENT.</p>\r\n<p>D&rsquo;TIGERS WERE HOPING TO GET A SECOND CONTINENTAL TITLE AND ACTUALLY STARTED WELL, WINNING THE FIRST QUARTER 14-8 DESPITE PLAYING THE HOME TEAM.</p>\r\n<p>HOWEVER, TUNISIA GOT THEIR BEARING AFTER THE POOR START; WINNING THE NEXT TWO QUARTERS</p>\r\n<p>17-10, 27-16.</p>\r\n<p>ATTEMPT BY D&rsquo;TIGERS TO FIGHT BACK IN THE LAST QUARTER ENDED ALL SQUARE AT 25-25, THEREBY FALLING TO 77-65 TO THE NORTH AFRICANS WHO</p>\r\n<p>WERE IN THE FINAL FOR THE FIRST TIME, DESPITE HOSTING THE COMPETITION THREE TIMES.</p>\r\n<p>DESPITE THE LOSS, D&rsquo;TIGERS WERE GALLANT IN DEFEAT AND WOULD BE PROUD OF THEIR PERFORMANCE IN THE PAST TWO WEEKS.</p>\r\n<p>THE 2015 CHAMPIONS WHO WERE JUST IN CAMP FOR TWO WEEKS SURPASSED THEIR PRE-TOURNAMENT EXPECTATIONS BY GETTING TO THE FINALS, DEFEATING CONTINENTAL POWERHOUSES LIKE SENEGAL AND CAMEROON IN THE QUARTER FINAL AND SEMIFINAL.</p>\r\n<p>CAPTAIN, IKE DIOGU WAS VOTED THE MOST VALUABLE PLAYER OF THE TOURNAMENT AFTER EMERGING AS THE LEADING SCORER WITH AN AVERAGE OF 22 POINTS PER GAME AND A TOTAL OF 132 POINTS WHILE NIGERIAN GUARD IKENNA IROEGBU WAS ALSO NAMED IN THE TOURNAMENT&rsquo;S BEST FIVE.</p>\r\n<p>SENEGAL BEAT MOROCCO 73-62 IN THE THIRD-PLACE MATCH.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>MEANWHILE, SLOVENIA HAS WON ITS FIRST-EVER EUROBASKET CHAMPIONSHIP, DEFEATING SERBIA 93-85 ON SUNDAY IN ISTANBUL. TRADITIONAL BASKETBALL POWERHOUSE SERBIA HAD TAKEN A 22-20 LEAD AT THE END OF THE FIRST QUARTER.</p>\r\n<p>SLOVENIA CAPTAIN AND MIAMA HEAT PLAYER GORAN DRAGIC TOOK CHARGE IN THE SECOND PERIOD AND WENT ON TO FINISH THE GAME WITH 35 POINTS</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>, SEVEN REBOUNDS, AND THREE ASSISTS TO</p>\r\n<p>BE</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>VOTED MOST VALUABLE PLAYER.<br /> .</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 20, '2017-09-20 06:11:01'),
(120, 'WITHOUT TINYMICE', '   NTA NETWORK NEWS				18TH September, 2017.\r\nGO/CS	===LOG===\r\nNEWSCASTER: ISAAC NKUMA \r\nPROD. EDITOR: GABRIEL ODU\r\nPRODUCER: CYRIL STOBER\r\n\r\nSOURCE	STORY TITLE	DUR\r\n	=OPENING MONTAGE/TEASER=	\r\nNEW YORK 	BUHARI AT UN GENERAL ASSEMBLY	\r\nPH	NORTHERN GOVS VISIT WIKE	\r\nAWKA	HAUSA COMMUNITIES PAY SOLIDARITY VISIT TO GOV OBIANO	\r\nABUJA	COAS APPRAISES ARMY OPERATIONS	\r\n\r\nABUJA \r\n\r\n              	UNHRC ON SITUATION OF NORTH EAST AWARD\r\n\r\n	\r\nABUJA	==STUDIO INTERVIEW==\r\nZANNA MUSTAPHA	\r\nABUJA	 NTA ONLINE PROMO==	\r\nABUJA	===1ST COMMERCIAL BREAK==	\r\n		\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n===PART TWO===\r\nABUJA	CJN CALLS FOR OBEDIENCE TO COURT JUDGEMENTS	\r\n\r\nABUJA	34TH EXPERT REVIEW MEETING ON POLIO	\r\nILORIN	KWARA FRSC COMMISSIONED	\r\nLAGOS 	LIVE REPORTS ETC.	\r\nLAGOS	2ND COMMERCIAL	\r\n		\r\n \r\n\r\n===PART THREE===\r\nABUJA	BUSINESS NEWS	\r\nABUJA	CTTEE ON STATISTICS INAUGURATED	\r\nABUJA	NNPC ASSURES NIGERIANS OF ADEQUATE PRODUCTS  -COPY	\r\nABUJA	STAKEHOLDERS CONSULTATION ON ELECTRICITY TARIFF LTP	\r\nKADUNA	===LIVE REPORTS===	\r\nBENIN	===LIVE REPORTS===	\r\nABUJA	===3RD COMMERCIAL===	\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n===PART FOUR===\r\nABUJA	FOREIGN NEWS	\r\nABUJA	SPORTS UPDATE	\r\nABUJA	OBITUARY DR. SYLVESTER OHO AYIH 	\r\nABUJA	WEATHER REPORT	\r\n	===ONLINE CLOSING===	\r\n\r\n	\r\n \r\n\r\nNTA NETWORK NEWS				18TH September, 2017.\r\nGO/CS	===STATES LOG===\r\n LAGOS:\r\n1.	Menace of trailess in Lagos\r\n2.	Pensioners Verification Commences\r\n3.	(Sports)  DTigers hosted by NBBF.\r\n	Newscaster:...Ademola Adeoye\r\nKADUNA:\r\n1.	Airforce inaugurates another batch of Special Forces.\r\n2.	Federal government raises 100 billion naira to finance road \r\n	projects .\r\n	Newscaster:.... Suleiman Abdullahi Rigachikun.\r\n\r\nBENIN:\r\n1.	APC committee on true federalism holds consultative forum in\r\n	Benin.  -1.25\r\n2.	Governor Obaseki Inspects Benin Auchi Road. - 1.03\r\n	Newscaster:..... Ogochukwuka Onah\r\nEve.\r\n \r\n\r\nNTA NETWORK NEWS				18TH September, 2017.\r\nGO/CS	===JOINING KADUNA===\r\nANN ON CAM:	Abdullahi is standing by with reports trending in Kaduna.\r\n	Over to you Abdullahi.\r\n \r\n	 \r\nEve.\r\n \r\n\r\nNTA NETWORK NEWS				18TH September, 2017.\r\nGO/CS	ABUJA:\r\n	VTR\r\nANN ON CAM:\r\n	===TRACK UP===\r\n	Cue out....NTA News\r\nEve.\r\n \r\n\r\nNTA NETWORK NEWS				18TH September, 2017.\r\nUA/CS	ABUJA: STAKEHOLDERS CONSULTATION ON ELECTRICITY TARIFF -LTP\r\n	VTR\r\nANN ON CAM:	Discussions are on to review multi  year tariff order to allow proper funding of the power sector and also be fair for social and economic development.\r\n	Correspondent Usman Aliyu reports that the consultation forum to that effect is led by the Nigerian Electricity Regulatory Commission in Abuja and other  geo-political zones.  \r\n	===TRACK UP===\r\n	Cue out....NTA News\r\nEve.\r\n \r\n\r\nNTA NETWORK NEWS				18TH September, 2017.\r\nASI/CS	ABUJA: DEMOCRATIC YOUTH CONGRESS FOR BUHARI BRIEFING\r\n	VTR\r\nANN ON CAM:	The Democratic Youth Congress for Buhari has demanded for immediate arrest and prosecution of Namdi Kanu, leader of the proscribed Independent people of Biafra for attempting to throw Nigeria into another civil war.\r\n	The group stated this at a media briefing in Abuja.\r\n	Abdullahi Sulayman Iyaji reports.\r\n	===TRACK UP===\r\n	Cue out....NTA News\r\nEve.\r\n \r\n\r\nNTA NETWORK NEWS				18TH September, 2017.\r\nTY/AYO/CS	ABUJA: FREEDOM AND JUSTICE MOVEMENT ON ONE NIGERIA\r\n	VTR\r\nANN ON CAM:	There are more resolves by Nigerians to resist every attempt to plunge Nigeria into crisis, disintegration or War.\r\n	One of the latest resolutions is from the freedom and justice movement, a political pressure group awaiting registration as a political party  from the Independent National Electoral Commission.\r\n	Timothy Yusuf reports.\r\n	===TRACK UP===\r\n	Cue out....NTA News\r\nEve.\r\n \r\n\r\nNTA NETWORK NEWS				18TH September, 2017.\r\nGO/CS	ABUJA:  AFAC CHOSING\r\n	VTR\r\nANN ON CAM:	After three weeks of display of Arts and Cultural Heritage, players in the Sector are optimistic more than ever, that it has the potential to serve as an alternative to oil and gas.\r\n	Musa Abubakar who was at the closing of the African Arts and Crafts Expo AFAC reports that the people also believe it holds the key to peaceful coexistence.\r\n	===TRACK UP===\r\n	Cue out....NTA News\r\nEve.\r\n \r\n\r\nNTA NETWORK NEWS				18TH September, 2017.\r\nFO/GO/CS	ABUJA: CJN CALLS FOR OBEDIENCE TO COURT JUDGEMENTS\r\n	VTR\r\nANN ON CAM:	A new legal year has commenced for the Supreme Court of Nigeria with the Chief Justice of Nigeria, Justice Walter Onnoghen calling for the pronouncement of the Nations courts to be respected and complied with.\r\n	Judiciary correspondent, Femi Okeowo reports on this and other activities that accompanied the\r\nRoll	new legal year.\r\n	===TRACK UP===\r\n	Cue out....NTA News\r\nEve.\r\n \r\n\r\nNTA NETWORK NEWS				18TH September, 2017.\r\nGO/CS	ILORIN:  KWARA FRSC COMMISSIONING \r\n	VTR\r\nANN ON CAM:	Reduction of carnage on Nigerian roads is achievable with cooperation of key players on safety, road users, and government at all levels.\r\n	Corps Marshal Federal Road Safety Corp Boboye  Oyeyemi made this known at the Commissioning of the Sector Command Office Complex in Ilorin.\r\n	Deborah Agboola has the details.\r\n	===TRACK UP===\r\n	Cue out....NTA News\r\nEve.\r\n \r\n\r\nNTA NETWORK NEWS				18TH September, 2017.\r\nMD/KF/GO/CS	ABUJA: COMMITTEE ON STATISTICS INAUGURATED\r\n	VTR\r\nANN ON CAM:	The Federal Government through the Ministry of Finance has inaugurated a Finance sectoral Consultative Committee on Statistics to coordinate Finance Statistics Production in the Country.\r\n	Muplang Dakok reports that the Committee was inaugurated by the Acting Permanent Secretary of the Ministry of Finance.\r\n	===TRACK UP===\r\n	Cue out....NTA News\r\nEve.\r\n \r\n\r\nNTA NETWORK NEWS				18TH September, 2017.\r\nMI/GO/CS	ABUJA: FCTA ON LAND ALLOCATION\r\n	VTR\r\nANN ON CAM:	The FCT Administration has cautioned Nigerians seeking land allocation in Abuja against patronizing local chiefs or area council offices, stating that only the FCT Minister is vested with the power of the President to allocate land in the FCT.\r\n	FCT Director of Land Administration, Adamu Jibrin emphasized this during an interview on latest land reforms of the FCT Administration.\r\n	Mitaire Ikpen reports.\r\n	===TRACK UP===\r\n	Cue out....NTA News\r\nEve.\r\n \r\n\r\nNTA NETWORK NEWS				18TH September, 2017.\r\nKN/GO/CS	ABUJA: UGANDAN OPPOSITION IN PARLIAMENT WORKSHOP\r\n	VTR\r\nANN ON CAM:	Participants at a workshop on effective opposition in parliament for Ugandan Parliamentarians have emphasized the importance of the views of the opposition in decision making process in the sustenance of a functional democracy of any nation.\r\n	National Assembly correspondent Kenneth Nanim reports that the workshop is organized by the National Institute for Legislative Studies, NILS.\r\n	===TRACK UP===\r\n	Cue out....NTA News\r\nEve.\r\nNTA NETWORK NEWS				18TH September, 2017.\r\nGO/CS	ABUJA: BUSINESS NEWS\r\n	VTR\r\nANN ON CAM:	Economic observer applauds FG over concessioning of Lagos, Abuja Airports as oil prices slip, but hold near recent highs in the global market.\r\n	Joy Uzor has details on business news. \r\n	===TRACK UP===\r\n	Cue out....NTA News\r\nEve.\r\n \r\n\r\nNTA NETWORK NEWS				18TH September, 2017.\r\nGO/CS	ABUJA:\r\n	VTR\r\nANN ON CAM:\r\n	===TRACK UP===\r\n	Cue out....NTA News\r\nEve.\r\n \r\n\r\nNTA NETWORK NEWS				18TH September, 2017.\r\nGO/CS	===INTRO TO STUDIO DISCUSSIONS===\r\nANN ON CAM:	Joining me now is Zannah Mustapha a lawyer and founder of future  prowess Islamic foundation school and the 2017 UNHCR Nansen Refugee award winner.\r\nQUESTION:\r\n1.	What was the inspiration for this humanitarian work that won\r\n	you the UNHCR Award?\r\n2.	How is it like taking care and educating Orphans, Widows and\r\n	the Less privileged? \r\n3.	You were the Mediator between the government and Boko\r\n	Haram Militants for the release of the first 103 School Girls,\r\n	What was it like?\r\n4.	Follow up (if any)\r\nNTA NETWORK NEWS				18TH September, 2017.\r\nGO/CS	PH: NOTHERN GOVERNORS FORUM VISIT WIKE\r\n	VTR\r\nANN ON CAM:	the Northern governors Forum has called for peaceful co-existence among Nigerians irrespective of ethnic or religious affiliation.\r\n	Governor of Borno State, Alhaji Kashim Shettima made the call when he led some members of the forum to Rivers State Government House on a courtesy visit.\r\n	Ogechi Nyekwere reports.\r\n	===TRACK UP===\r\n	Cue out....NTA News\r\nEve.\r\n \r\n\r\nNTA NETWORK NEWS				18TH September, 2017.\r\nGO/CS	AWKA: HAUSA  COMMUNITIES PAY SOLIDARITY VISIT TO GOV. OBIANO\r\n	VTR\r\nANN ON CAM:	Members of Hausa Communities resident in various parts of Anambra state under the aegis of Arewa Community have paid a solidarity visit to Governor Willie Obiano in Awka.\r\n	Benson Osadebe reports that members of the delegation expressed satisfaction with what they described as the Governors humane disposition towards non Anambra indigenes.\r\n	===TRACK UP===\r\n	Cue out....NTA News\r\nEve.\r\n \r\n\r\nNTA NETWORK NEWS				18TH September, 2017.\r\nGO/CS	===INTRO TO STUDIOS===\r\nANN ON CAM:	Good evening and welcome to NTA Network News, I am Isaac Nkuma.\r\n	In Lagos is Ademola Adeoye.\r\n	In Kaduna is Suleiman Abdullahi Rigachikun and in Benin is Ogochukwuka Onah.\r\n	 \r\nEve.\r\n \r\n\r\nNTA NETWORK NEWS				18TH September, 2017.\r\nGO/CS	===3rd PROMO===\r\nANN ON CAM:	Up next is  Foreign Sports and Weather, when we return.\r\n	 \r\nEve.\r\n \r\n\r\nNTA NETWORK NEWS				18TH September, 2017.\r\nGO/CS	===JOINING LAGOS===\r\nANN ON CAM:	Lets go over to our  Lagos Network Centre, Ademola is standing by with more reports.\r\n	 \r\nEve.\r\n \r\n\r\nNTA NETWORK NEWS				18TH September, 2017.\r\nGO/CS	===JOINING BENIN===\r\nANN ON CAM:	Lets join Ogochukwuka in Benin for more reports.\r\n	Good to see you Ogochukwuka.\r\n	 \r\nEve.\r\n \r\n\r\nNTA NETWORK NEWS				18TH September, 2017.\r\nGO/CS	===TEASER===\r\n	===TRACK UP===\r\n1/*************	Ahead of United Nations General Assembly  President Buhari arrives in New York.\r\n	=====================================\r\n	===TRACK UP===\r\n2/.************	Respect the Pronouncements of the Nations Courts Thats the advice of the Chief Justice of Nigeria as new legal year commences and new silks are inducted.\r\n	=====================================\r\n3/.*************	Hausa Community in Anambra pays solidarity visit to Gov. Willie Obiano. \r\n	Just as Northern governors go to Port Harcourt. \r\nEve.\r\nNTA NETWORK NEWS				18TH September, 2017.\r\nGO/CS	===PROMO ONE===\r\nANN ON CAM:	Still to come, New silks are inaugurated as Chief Justice of Nigeria call for respect for Court pronouncements.\r\n	 \r\nEve.\r\n \r\n\r\nNTA NETWORK NEWS				18TH September, 2017.\r\nPR/EJJ/GO/CS	ABUJA: NNPC ASSURES NIGERIANS OF ADEQUATE PRODUCTS. -COPY \r\nANN ON CAM:	The Nigerian National Petroleum Corporation, NNPC, has assured the public not to engage in\r\nGraphics	panic buying of Petroleum products that they have enough to serve the Nation for 48 days.\r\n	This is contained in a statement by the Corporations, Group General Manager Public Affairs Ndu Ughamadu.\r\n	NNPC therefore advised motorists to report any challenge in the course of purchasing to the Department of Petroleum Resources, DPR.\r\n	In a similar press release Ndu Ughamadu said the fire at the Apapa loading Jetty, Lagos would not affect the supply of the products.\r\n	In explained that the fire sparked off from the activities of hoodlums who were scooping fuels spilled from a ship discharging fuel at the Jetty.\r\n\r\nNTA NETWORK NEWS				18TH September, 2017.\r\nGO/CS	ABUJA: OBITUARY: SYLVESTER OHO AYIH -COPY \r\n\r\nANN ON CAM:	The death has been announced of a Traditional Ruler, Dr. Sylvester Oho Ayih, the Abaga Toni of Toni Clriefdom, Kokona local Government, Nasarawa State.\r\nGraphics:	Aged 90, Dr. Sylvester Ayih died on the second of this Month.\r\n	He was an educationist, Pioneer Provost, College of Education, Akwanga and a onetime Permanent Secretary in the old Plateau State.\r\n	A statement by the family source says the remains will be buried tomorrow, at his palace in Garaku, Kokona local government, Nasarawa state.\r\n	He is survived by a wife, Children and many grand children.\r\n	#\r\nEve.\r\n NTA NETWORK NEWS				18TH September, 2017.\r\nGO/CS	LAGOS: INFO MINISTER ON IPOB \r\n	VTR\r\nANN ON CAM:	The FG says the IPOB is using fake videos for mass killings harvested from other parts of Africa and doctored to look current to mislead the International Community of ongoing genocide in the country to win their support.\r\n	Information & Culture Minister Lai Mohammed states this when he addressed online publishers in Lagos.\r\n	===TRACK UP===\r\n	Cue out....NTA News\r\nEve.\r\n\r\n \r\n \r\n\r\nNTA NETWORK NEWS				18TH September, 2017.\r\nPR/IN/GO/CS	ABUJA: INAUGURATION OF SALARIES AND WAGES BOARD - COPY \r\nANN ON CAM:	The Board of National Salaries, Incomes and Wages will be inaugurated on Tuesday the nineteenth of September, 2017 at the office of the Secretary to the Government of the\r\nCaption	Federation.\r\n	A statement signed by the Assistant Director Press, Office of the Secretary to the Government of the Federation Mohammed Nakorji says the appointed board members are expected to participate in the inauguration ceremony.\r\n	The statement further adds that guests, Chairman of the Commission and the Board members should be seated in the SGFS conference room by half past ten in the morning.\r\nEve.	#.\r\n  ', 17, '2017-09-20 06:20:08'),
(121, 'GMN RIPPLES OF PYTHON DANCE', '<p><strong><u>GMN RIPPLES OF PYTHON DANCE </u></strong></p>\r\n<p>DIRECTOR, DEFENCE INFORMATION, MAJOR GENERAL JOHN ENENCHE HAS ASSURED THE PUBLIC THAT CONFIRMED CASES OF HUMAN RIGHT VIOLATIONS AMONG THE ARMED FORCES WILL NOT GO UNPUNISHED</p>\r\n<p>AWARE HOWEVER THAT INTERNET, PHOTOSHOPPING CAN ALTER FACTS HE SAYS THE MILITARY IS INVESTIGATING THE ALLEGATIONS.</p>\r\n<p>CORRESPONDENT LYDIA SAMSON HAS THE REPORT</p>\r\n<p><strong><u>&nbsp;</u></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><u>NARRATION</u></strong></p>\r\n<p>GENERAL ENENCHE WAS ON GOOD MORNING NIGERIA, DISCUSSING THE RIPPLE OF ONGOING MILITARY OPERATIONS. HE URGED &nbsp;THE PUBLIC TO BE PATIENT WITH OPERATION PYTHON DANCE IN THE SOUTH &nbsp;EAST</p>\r\n<p>THE GENERAL REITERATED THE FACT THAT THE MILITARY WILL NOT CONDONE THREATS FROM ANY GROUP, STATING THAT MILITARY EXERCISE IS NORMAL AND NECESSARY TO BUILD CITIZENS CONFIDENCE.</p>\r\n<p><strong>TRACK UP </strong></p>\r\n<p>SPEAKING ON IPOB , GENERAL ENENCHE SAID THE GROUP HAD BECOME MILITANT ,TERRORISING PEOPLE, &nbsp;BLOCKING ROADS AND DISRUPTING PEACE.</p>\r\n<p><strong>TRACK UP </strong></p>\r\n<p>HE COMMENDED THE SOUTH EAST GOVERNORS FOR THE POSITION TAKEN TO BROKER PEACE AND GAURANTEE SECURITY OF LIVES AND PROPERTY.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 17, '2017-09-20 19:05:09'),
